parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint of the driver or passenger, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract into the door
the seat belt does not restrain the driver or passenger
the seat belt fails to deploy properly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission's failure to downshift smoothly can cause sudden jerks, loss of control, and unexpected slowing, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The transmission drops into low gear unexpectedly
the front wheels squeal and slide
the transmission jumps into a lower gear
